  "doc_id": "39333",
  "text": "While not typically considered for their role in immunity, recent studies have demonstrated that neurons, particularly sensory neurons, can function to alert surrounding tissues to infection or damage and directly sense microbes [CITATION_1] . Whether neurons in the brain become damaged by C. neoformans infection or are able to sense and respond to this damage is not known; however, it is interesting to note that strict control of copper homeostasis is needed to maintain neuronal health [CITATION_2] , which may impact on C. neoformans pathogenesis within the brain.",
